==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tapish
<hw>Tap"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[F. se
<ets>tapir</ets> to squat.]</ety> <def>To lie close to the ground, so as
to be concealed; to squat; to crouch; hence, to hide one's self.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>tappis</asp>, <asp>tappish</asp>,
<asp>tappice</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As a hound that, having roused a hart,⟦br⟧
Although he <qex>tappish</qex> ne'er so soft.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taplash</ent>⟦br⟧
